main event: Observers watched two similar bright objects in the sky for approximately 2 hours, which were later identified as Venus and Jupiter.
interesting points: The objects were described as appearing like aluminum plates spinning or tumbling., Observers reported that the objects were very bright and visible lower than the stars., The event occurred on August 7, 1966, at 0320z., Witnesses included a husband and wife who watched the objects from their porch until dawn., A sketch of the observed objects was later submitted to Project Blue Book.
sighted object: two bright objects in the sky
witness description: A couple, the husband being a city director, with prior scientific experience.
